<item>
            <title>[FLINK-28976] Changelog 1st materialization delayed unneccesarily</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-28976</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In PeriodicMaterializationManager.start(), the 1st materialization is scheduled with a delay: materialization_interval + random_offset &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here, random_offset is added to avoid thundering herd problem.&lt;br/&gt;
The next materialization will be scheduled with a delay of only materialization_interval.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That means that the 1st materialization will have to compact up to 2 times more state changes than the subsequent ones. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which in turn can cause FLINK--26590 or other problems.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
